latestPosts.caption:
The story behind this lehenga: I had just a few weeks before my wedding and was still missing one outfit. I saw a picture of this @anitadongre lehenga on Instagram and immediately messaged them. With so little time there was no way to get the piece made (they need 4 months for any brides who are wedding planning). I was told that they didn’t have it on hand and had pretty much given up on getting it. And then suddenly the Delhi store reached out to me. They had located one piece and it was in my size! They shipped it to Hyderabad, we did some minor alterations, and I had it ready the week before the wedding 🎉 It all truly worked in my favor to have this gorgeous piece in time 😊
.
.

latestPosts.caption:
Save this Aswan gem for your Egypt trip! @katodool is perched on the hillside of a Nubian Village with panoramic Nile views. When you’re ready to explore, you’re just steps from the Nubian Village and a short drive to Abu Simbel, Philae Temple and other Aswan treasures. The name “Kato Dool” means “The Big Home” in Nubian - and it truly feels like one.

latestPosts.caption:
One of my favorite temples built by Ramesses II - one for himself and another for his beloved wife Nefertari! An engineering marvel that lets sunlight enter 200ft deep into the sanctuary twice a year, lighting up the pharaoh sitting among the gods 
.

Pro tip: Book a day tour from Aswan - worth setting aside most of the day for this incredible sight! 🚗

latestPosts.caption:
This temple survived: 
✨ Getting partially destroyed
✨ Having its owner’s name chiseled off walls 
✨ Nearly 3500 years of desert weather 
✨ Multiple attempts to erase its builder from history. Yet here we are, still talking about how Hatshepsut was one of Egypt’s most successful pharaoh’s who turned her reign into Egypt’s golden age. 
.
#hatshepsut #luxor #ancientegypt #luxortemple #womeninhistory #travelegypt #wanderluster
